<ue5><m0>Hundreds attend funeral<ql>
for officer slain on duty<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>  <m0>ST-EUSTACHE, Quebec <m0>(--) Hundreds of police officers from all over North America gathered Friday for the funeral of a Montreal constable fatally shot as he stopped a motorist on a routine traffic check.<ep>
   The officers crowded into the Eglise St-Eustache church in this community north of Montreal to pay last respects to Andre Lalonde.<ep>
   Lalonde, 51, was gunned down Monday morning on a quiet residential street in the Montreal suburb of Senneville.<ep>
   Lalonde, who was to retire at the end of this year, was shot three times. Police think he had stopped the motorist because of a noisy muffler.<ep>
    Police arrested a man Wednesday and questioned him in connection with the killing. He has not been charged in the death but was charged with armed robbery.<ql>
