<ue5><m0>Taxi driver dies 29 months<ql>
after beating by police<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>MONTREAL <m0>(--) A Montreal taxi driver who was beaten into unconsciousness while in police custody 29 months ago has died.<ep>
   Richard Barnabe, 41, died Thursday evening from internal bleeding, his sister Claudette said Friday.<ep>
   The cabbie collapsed in police cells in December 1993 after being arrested for leading police on a wild car chase when they responded to a broken church window in nearby Laval. Barnabe was unconscious when he was admitted to the hospital and he remained there in a vegetative state until he died.<ep>
   Four Montreal police officers were convicted of assault causing bodily harm. They are appealing the verdict and have not served any time in jail. A fifth officer was acquitted.<ql>
