<ue5><m0>U.S. jobs report reassures<ql>
stock market on interest rates<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>  <m0>TORONTO <m0>(--) Canadian stocks rose after a U.S. jobs report eased concern that inflation will accelerate and cause interest rates to rise soon, analysts said.<ep>
   Alcan Aluminium Ltd., Newbridge Networks Corp. and Canadian Pacific Ltd. led the Toronto Stock Exchange 300 Composite Index up 7.31 points to 5124.50.<ep>
   Stocks gained after the Labor Department said the U.S. economy created 2,000 nonfarm jobs in April, much less than the 117,000 forecast by analysts.<ep>
   A rise in interest rates by the United States (--) Canada's largest trading partner (--) likely would prompt an increase in Canadian rates.<ep>
   The U.S. dollar closed Friday at C$1.3652; the Canadian dollar closed at U.S. 73.25 cents.<ql>
